447.622.  Petition, requirements. — Any organization may petition to have property declared abandoned pursuant to the provisions of sections 447.620 to 447.640 and for temporary possession of such property, if:
  (1)  The property has been continuously unoccupied by persons legally entitled to possession for at least six months prior to the filing of the petition;
  (2)  The taxes are delinquent on the property;
  (3)  The property is a nuisance; and
  (4)  The organization intends to rehabilitate the property.
(L. 1993 S.B. 376 § 2, A.L. 1994 S.B. 513, A.L. 2002 H.B. 1634 merged with S.B. 1086 & 1126, A.L. 2005 H.B. 58)
